style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (EOR/EGR)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in some circumstances.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Q2:  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What contribution could CCS make towards th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">e UK’s decarbonisatio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">n targets?  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Are the UK Government’s expectations reasonable in this regard?</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">CCS could make a huge contribution to reducing the UK’s CO</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> emissions. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Fossil fuels currently</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (2012)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> provide</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 70</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">% of the UK’s electricity and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> if all of this generation was replaced by coal</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> or gas</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">-fired generation</span><sp